---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pest Control Smithfield | Rentals, JCU, Recurring Plans"
  description="Pest control in Smithfield, Cairns — general pest, cockroaches, ants, rodents and termites for the northern beaches gateway, JCU and rental stock. Recurring tropical plans, free quote."
  canonical="https://cairnspestmanagement.com.au/smithfield/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Smithfield &middot; northern beaches gateway &middot; JCU &middot; rentals</span>
      <h1>Pest control in <span class="accent">Smithfield</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Smithfield is the gateway to the northern beaches &mdash; home to James
        Cook University, the regional shopping hub, and a large share of rental
        and student housing. That mix means turnover, shared walls and constant
        tropical pest pressure, so recurring pest contracts are the norm here. We
        cover general pest, cockroaches, ants, rodents and termites.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Smithfield</span>
      <h2>Pest control for the northern beaches gateway.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Rental and student stock means recurring contracts.</h3>
        <p>
          With JCU and the Smithfield shopping precinct on the doorstep, a big
          chunk of housing here is <strong>rental and student accommodation</strong>
          &mdash; units, share houses and townhouse complexes with high turnover
          between tenants. Pests do not respect a change of tenancy, so the smart
          play is a <strong>recurring pest plan</strong>: a vacate or end-of-lease
          treatment between tenants, plus scheduled servicing on the building. Many
          Smithfield landlords and property managers keep us on an ongoing
          contract for exactly this reason.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cockroaches and ants are the headline.</h3>
        <p>
          The bread-and-butter Smithfield job is <strong>cockroaches and
          ants</strong>. German cockroaches travel between units in shared kitchens
          and laundries, and tropical ants stream in from the gardens and
          landscaping. We treat with gel baits and a residual barrier, and on
          multi-unit complexes we treat the shared harbourage so the problem does
          not just bounce from one unit to the next &mdash; see
          <a href="/services/cockroach-ant-control/">cockroach &amp; ant control</a>
          and <a href="/services/general-pest-control/">general pest control</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Rodents, termites and the JCU edge.</h3>
        <p>
          Smithfield backs onto bushland and creek lines near the university, which
          adds rodent and termite pressure. The wet season pushes rats and mice into
          roof voids (<a href="/services/rodent-control/">rodent control</a>), and
          the bushland edge keeps Coptotermes and Mastotermes termites active &mdash;
          older Smithfield homes and any property near the reserve should be on an
          annual <a href="/services/termite-control/">termite inspection</a> to
          AS&nbsp;3660. Body-corporate complexes can roll all of this into one
          managed program.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Smithfield jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>End-of-lease / vacate pest treatment between tenants (~$215&ndash;$320)</li>
          <li>Recurring pest contract for a rental portfolio or body-corporate complex</li>
          <li>German cockroach clean-out across a share-house kitchen with follow-up (~$215&ndash;$290)</li>
          <li>Wet-season rodent baiting and roof-void proofing near the creek lines (~$180&ndash;$350)</li>
          <li>AS 3660 annual termite inspection on a bushland-edge home (~$235&ndash;$380)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/edmonton/">Edmonton</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/redlynch/">Redlynch</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/trinity-beach/">Trinity Beach</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/earlville/">Earlville</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cairns-region/">All Cairns Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Smithfield pest control quote.</h2>
        <p>General pest, cockroaches, ants, rodents and termites. Recurring contracts for rentals and complexes.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
